reviewText: A great movie for all to see - Tatum O'Neal won a best supporting actress and she should have.

Well deserved 5 stars!!! This 1973 flick deserved way more attention than the Oscar Tatum O'Neal received. I really feel it's a timeless period flick because the subject matter is still relevant today. With Bogdanovich filming it in black and white, along with the landscape and vehicles you get transformed to that depression era seamlessly.
